%description:
On handover the new MAG re-registers the mobile node. [Required -- RFC 5213 6.9.1.1]

When the mobile node moves from one access gateway to another, the new serving MAG detects the
attachment and sends its own Proxy Binding Update to the LMA, which updates the binding to point the
tunnel at the new MAG -- all without any signalling from the node. The node roams from mag1 to mag2;
observed on the wire at mag2's backhaul interface as it transmits a Proxy Binding Update after the
move.

%file: Pmipv6_Handover.cc

#include "ProtocolTest.h"

namespace inet {
namespace protocoltest {

Define_ProtocolTest(ipv6_pmipv6_handover)
{
    return ProtocolTest("ipv6_pmipv6_handover")
        .once(on("mag2.eth[0].mac").signal("packetSentToLower")
                  .packet("BindingUpdate.proxyRegistrationFlag == true")
                  .describe("mag2's Proxy Binding Update after the handover").notBefore(20).within(50));
}

} // namespace protocoltest
} // namespace inet

%inifile: test.ini

[General]
*.tester.testName = "ipv6_pmipv6_handover"
include ../../ini/_pmipv6.ini

%contains: stdout
PROTOCOLTEST ipv6_pmipv6_handover: PASS
